args:
When Graht learns that Regina is Origa's sister,
he orders the former's assassination.
Meanwhile, Regina is reunited with her
confiscated tablet, and she uses it to turn the
tables on Graht's men before signaling the
angels and apostles to begin their operation.
One day, I gained a sister.

She was much younger and not related by blood.
My parent married hers, and suddenly we were
family. At first, I wasn't sure how to approach her
given the age gap, but we were soon inseparable.
We may have been stepsisters, but we were\nstill as close as any blood siblings could be.\n...Until the day everything changed.

Our village, Alphir, stood in the path of a raging
war and was burned to ash in a single night.
The heat of the fire. The burning in my throat.
The cries for help. The smell of seared flesh.
My happy life crumbled before my very eyes.
I'd held my sister's hand every day since we\nfirst met, but on that day...I let go.
...And I have regretted it ever since.\nNot a day goes by where I don't ask myself\nwhy I did it. How I COULD have done it.
I fled a war. I nearly starved to death in\nthe lowest slum of Grams. And yet all that\ntime, you were the only thing in my mind.
How long I have wanted to apologize!
An apology is hardly necessary.\nIf anything, I'm grateful.

It is true my life changed when we parted.
Days of crawling through the mud.
Drinking from puddles.
Eating rotting carcasses...
And things did not get better even when I\nwas taken in by the orphanage or when my\naptitude as an Auspex was discovered.
It was one horror after the next, and I\nwished for death more times than I know.\nYet here I am, still very much alive.
I survived agonizing training. Survived the\nviper's den of the other Auspex candidates.\nAnd in the end, I claimed the title.
Now here I stand, Her Holiness the Pope.\nAnd it is all thanks to you, dear sister.
That day you shook loose my hand,\nyou helped me realize something\nof paramount importance...
A person must reach out and claim\nhappiness for themselves!
Thank you. Now I have nothing left unsaid.\nI am fine on my own, and here our\nconversation will end.
You're right, Origa. Everyone has to find\ntheir own happiness.

When I learned you'd become the Auspex,
I also undertook training that nearly killed 
me—and I did so in the hopes I might see
you again.

My work earned me a place in the Canon
high enough to enter the Curia, and
eventually I was given command of
the apostles.
Well, I suppose my natural affinity for the\nangels played a part in that, so it feels\nstrange to claim all the credit...
But working with the apostles under me\ntaught me a new lesson...
We all must find our own happiness,\nbut that doesn't mean we have to do so\nwithout help.
Will you let me help you, Origa?\nWill you let your sister help you?
Guard, return this woman to her cell.
No, wait! Just one more thing, Origa.\nDo me this final kindness.
Will you return the tablet that was\nconfiscated when I was brought in?\nIt's terribly boring in that cell.
Do you seek to mock Her Holiness?\nShe would never grant such a thing!
It holds all the records of an experiment\nI was conducting, and I was interrupted\nat the most awkward and unsatisfying—
*sigh* It's fine. Give it to her.
Graht said it doesn't serve a purpose\noutside of magical analysis, so I fail\nto see the harm.
As you command. Now move along, you!
I'm glad we were able to speak\nin the end, Sister.
Hmm. I had no idea that Origa\nand Regina were sisters.
Still, I can't have Origa swayed by paltry\nsentimentality, so I'm afraid her dear\nsister will have to die.
Are you certain that's wise, Eminence?

If we kill her and are unable to ready a
replacement who is compatible with
Sandalphon's Sigil, it could mean losing
an angel.
What use has the Church for angels\nanymore? Now do as I command.
This the thing you were moaning about?
Yes, and thank you so very much!\n...And that's fallback number two.
If we're done here, get back in your—
What? Hey! What are you doing?!
You met the Auspex's compassion with\nbetrayal, knocked the guard unconscious,\nand fled. ...Or so the story will go.
Here to kill me, are you?\nOn Graht's orders, no doubt.
That isn't for you to know. Now, as a final\nact of piety, die quietly for the Church's\nglorious future.
Actually, I was just feeling a bit stiff, and\na workout sounds nice. So anyone who\nwants to be cut down, come at me!
Grams is just over that hill. We managed\nto get back in time for the Auspecalia.
There's no time, so I'll keep this brief.\nI'm using the new spell I was developing\nto speak to you from inside the Curia.
It's a little something I've been working on\nsince the angels' communication was cut\noff during the Paradise incident.

Still a work in progress, so it's a one-way
channel for now—which means I can't
hear anything you say, so save your breath
and just listen to me.
Pinon, if Nevin just called me names,\nreport it to me later. I've been saving an\nespecially obnoxious mission for him.
Okay, are we sure she can't hear us?!\nI KNOW YOU HEARD ME, REGINA!
It's highly likely that Cardinal Graht is\nbehind the series of demonic incidents\nthat we've been chasing.
He just sent his minions to try to kill me\nin an uncharacteristically direct and—\nfrankly—rather sloppy move.
That means he's past the point of needing\nto cover up his skulduggery, so his plans\nmust be entering their final stage of—
Sorry. Turns out there were more minions.\nBack to what I was saying.
Graht is likely planning something big\nto coincide with the Auspecalia today.
I don't know the details, but whatever it is,\nwe need to stop it at any cost—and I'm\ngoing to need your help.
I don't know whether this transmission is\nreaching you or not, but I'm acting on the\nassumption that it is.
I know you all trust me and won't question\nmy allegiances, because I feel the same\nabout you.
That bond of trust is my greatest asset, and\nthe irreplaceable pride of a professional\ncareer forged in blood, sweat, and tears.
And that's how I know this operation will\nsucceed. How could it not, with me at the\nhelm and all of you to execute it perfectly?
Anyway, that's the pep talk. I'd ask if\nyou're ready, but I can't hear you and I\nknow the answer anyway.
Now, as the hands of the Goddess,\ngo administer the hell out of Her authority!
